784
00:40:36,367 --> 00:40:38,970
Francoise, turn off the T.V.

785
00:40:39,104 --> 00:40:41,239
Go in the other room.
You're getting on my nerves.

786
00:40:41,372 --> 00:40:43,775
You cannot treat me
like a baby.

787
00:40:43,909 --> 00:40:45,143
(PHONE RINGING)

788
00:40:46,778 --> 00:40:48,113
Hello?

789
00:40:48,246 --> 00:40:50,649
Oh, yes, send her right on up,
please. Yeah. Thank you.

790
00:40:50,782 --> 00:40:51,750
It's Yakimoto.

791
00:40:51,883 --> 00:40:53,919
Harry, I want to meet her.

792
00:40:54,052 --> 00:40:56,888
I never met
a Japanese, uh,
journalist.

793
00:40:57,022 --> 00:40:58,990
Get in the other room now.

794
00:40:59,124 --> 00:41:00,492
No, no, no,
it's okay, Harry.

795
00:41:00,626 --> 00:41:02,227
Yakimoto's very nice.
She can meet her.

796
00:41:02,360 --> 00:41:03,995
No, I don't want her
to meet her.

797
00:41:04,129 --> 00:41:07,298
I want her to get on a plane
and go back to Paris.

798
00:41:08,800 --> 00:41:09,968
FRANCOISE: (SPEAKING FRENCH)

799
00:41:10,101 --> 00:41:11,169
NANCY:
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

800
00:41:11,302 --> 00:41:12,671
You wanna play dirty?

801
00:41:12,804 --> 00:41:14,640
Go home to your mother!

802
00:41:14,773 --> 00:41:18,176
You're cold,
just like the fruit of pickle!

803
00:41:18,309 --> 00:41:20,011
You're selfish!

804
00:41:20,145 --> 00:41:21,146
Oh, no.

805
00:41:21,279 --> 00:41:22,347
What are you doing?

806
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:23,749
(DOORBELL RINGS)
I hate you!

807
00:41:23,882 --> 00:41:24,850
Get back!

808
00:41:24,983 --> 00:41:27,018
No, no, no, no. Oh.

809
00:41:27,152 --> 00:41:28,419
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

810
00:41:29,655 --> 00:41:30,656
Hi, Nancy.
Hi.

811
00:41:30,789 --> 00:41:32,691
Oh.

812
00:41:32,824 --> 00:41:34,893
Is this a bad time?
No, no, come on in.

813
00:41:35,026 --> 00:41:36,294
Uh, hi.

814
00:41:36,995 --> 00:41:38,029
Hi.

815
00:41:38,163 --> 00:41:40,298
Yakimoto Yakimura,
this is Harry Stone.

816
00:41:40,431 --> 00:41:41,366
Well, hi, hi.

817
00:41:41,499 --> 00:41:42,834
Hello.

818
00:41:42,968 --> 00:41:44,870
It's like a... It's like
a scene from a movie.

819
00:41:45,003 --> 00:41:46,104
(CHUCKLES)

820
00:41:46,237 --> 00:41:49,374
Oh, have you ever done
a screwball comedy?

821
00:41:49,507 --> 00:41:52,043
I, uh, I thought
you're not a critic.

822
00:41:52,177 --> 00:41:53,344
(CHUCKLES)

823
00:41:53,478 --> 00:41:55,113
I'm not. Just a writer.
(DOORBELL RINGING)

824
00:41:55,246 --> 00:41:56,682
I made a couple
of visits to Japan.

825
00:41:56,815 --> 00:41:58,984
I liked it.
Everybody's uptight.

826
00:41:59,117 --> 00:42:01,553
I'm from Syracuse, New York.

827
00:42:01,687 --> 00:42:03,722
Do you mind
if I use a tape recorder?

828
00:42:03,855 --> 00:42:05,490
Whatever you want.

829
00:42:06,725 --> 00:42:08,359
Do you want to eat first?
Mmm-mmm.

830
00:42:08,493 --> 00:42:09,861
Ask away.

831
00:42:10,361 --> 00:42:11,362
(SIGHS)

832
00:42:14,365 --> 00:42:15,701
Why'd you move to France?

833
00:42:15,834 --> 00:42:18,369
Salami on rye?
Yeah,
that's for Mr. Stone.

834
00:42:18,503 --> 00:42:19,671
And the,
uh, cream soda?

835
00:42:19,805 --> 00:42:20,906
I got the soda.

836
00:42:21,039 --> 00:42:23,474
Yeah, now, I'll take
care of it, thank you.

837
00:42:23,609 --> 00:42:25,076
Yaki, can I get you
some coffee?

838
00:42:25,210 --> 00:42:26,845
Uh, yeah, sure.
Uh, black, no sugar.

839
00:42:26,978 --> 00:42:27,979
Okay.

840
00:42:28,113 --> 00:42:29,815
Oh.
Why'd I move to France?

841
00:42:29,948 --> 00:42:31,016
Yes.

842
00:42:32,383 --> 00:42:34,653
What about the, uh,
hot fudge sundae?

843
00:42:34,786 --> 00:42:35,821
I'll take care of it.

844
00:42:35,954 --> 00:42:38,924
Come and get
your ice cream.

845
00:42:39,057 --> 00:42:43,394
I moved to France because
I was tired of New York,

846
00:42:43,528 --> 00:42:45,797
and I refused
to live in L.A.

847
00:42:45,931 --> 00:42:48,600
Besides, why do you need
a reason to move
to a beautiful place?

848
00:42:48,734 --> 00:42:49,935
France is gorgeous.

849
00:42:50,068 --> 00:42:51,402
Seriously gorgeous.

850
00:42:51,536 --> 00:42:53,271
But you're an American.
Mmm-hmm.

851
00:42:55,506 --> 00:42:56,775
Francoise,
where are you going?

852
00:42:56,908 --> 00:42:57,909
Home.

853
00:42:58,043 --> 00:42:59,077
Come here.
No!

854
00:42:59,210 --> 00:43:00,612
Sit down,
have your hot fudge sundae.

855
00:43:00,746 --> 00:43:03,214
No, you cannot treat
me like a piece of shit!

856
00:43:03,348 --> 00:43:05,917
I'm sorry. I apologize.

857
00:43:07,052 --> 00:43:09,487
I'm, I'm nervous
about the movie,

858
00:43:09,621 --> 00:43:13,659
and I, I guess
I'm taking it out on you.

859
00:43:13,792 --> 00:43:15,727
Come on. You wanna sign
for this now, please?

860
00:43:15,861 --> 00:43:18,596
Sit down with Harry.
Come on. Sit in my lap,
come on.

861
00:43:18,730 --> 00:43:19,965
HARRY:
Where's the hot fudge?

862
00:43:20,098 --> 00:43:21,667
NANCY:
Yeah, there you are. Here.

863
00:43:22,267 --> 00:43:23,334
Here.

864
00:43:24,770 --> 00:43:26,137
Have a bite.

865
00:43:28,406 --> 00:43:29,741
Is it good?

866
00:43:30,075 --> 00:43:31,576
Hmm.

867
00:43:31,710 --> 00:43:34,813
HARRY:
Have a bite. (LAUGHS)
Where were we?

868
00:43:34,946 --> 00:43:36,815
Uh, "France
is seriously gorgeous."

869
00:43:36,948 --> 00:43:39,084
I'm from Paris.
Francoise Tournier.

870
00:43:39,217 --> 00:43:40,285
Yakimoto Yakimura.

871
00:43:40,418 --> 00:43:41,486
Hi.
Hello.

872
00:43:41,619 --> 00:43:43,989
I got fed up with
the New York bullshit.

873
00:43:44,122 --> 00:43:46,091
And I couldn't take
the swimming pool scene.

874
00:43:46,224 --> 00:43:47,959
That's not hard
to figure out, is it?

875
00:43:48,093 --> 00:43:49,627
Here.

876
00:43:49,761 --> 00:43:53,031
I, uh, I really like
that picture,
the Blue Dust.

877
00:43:53,164 --> 00:43:54,632
Thank you, amigo.

878
00:43:55,533 --> 00:43:56,634
(CHUCKLES)

879
00:43:56,768 --> 00:43:58,837
What do you know?
He saw Blue Dust.

880
00:43:58,970 --> 00:44:01,506
Are you here to stay,
Mr. Stone?

881
00:44:01,639 --> 00:44:02,674
Harry.
Harry.

882
00:44:02,808 --> 00:44:04,843
Here to live,
you mean?
Yeah.

883
00:44:04,976 --> 00:44:06,311
No, I have
no future plans.

884
00:44:06,444 --> 00:44:08,013
If anything,
I'm contemplating suicide.

885
00:44:08,146 --> 00:44:10,348
(CHUCKLES)
He's joking.

886
00:44:11,316 --> 00:44:12,784
No, he's not.

887
00:44:12,918 --> 00:44:15,186
He's very anxious
about The Pickle.

888
00:44:15,320 --> 00:44:16,454
Shut up, Francoise.

889
00:44:16,587 --> 00:44:18,389
Would you call
The Pickle a comedy?

890
00:44:18,523 --> 00:44:19,858
No, believe me,
it's a tragedy.

891
00:44:19,991 --> 00:44:21,793
This dentist should
go to jail for life.

892
00:44:21,927 --> 00:44:24,830
Phil, Phil,
meet Yakimoto Yakimura.

893
00:44:24,963 --> 00:44:26,131
This is my agent,
Phil Hirsch.

894
00:44:26,264 --> 00:44:27,532
Oh, hello.

895
00:44:27,665 --> 00:44:29,134
I'd better come back
later, Harry.

896
00:44:29,267 --> 00:44:30,535
Maybe I should
come back later.

897
00:44:30,668 --> 00:44:31,770
Hello, Francoise.

898
00:44:31,903 --> 00:44:34,505
Oh, no, no, continue
the interview, please.

899
00:44:35,841 --> 00:44:37,642
(CHUCKLES)

900
00:44:37,776 --> 00:44:41,112
Your films are sort
of like this scene
in the hotel room, Harry.

901
00:44:41,246 --> 00:44:42,480
Is that good or bad?

902
00:44:42,613 --> 00:44:44,415
I told you, I'm not a critic.

903
00:44:44,549 --> 00:44:46,517
So, what's next?

904
00:44:46,651 --> 00:44:48,720
Well, I don't know
what I'm gonna do next.

905
00:44:48,854 --> 00:44:50,055
I know what
I should have done.

906
00:44:50,188 --> 00:44:51,222
NANCY:
Harry.

907
00:44:51,356 --> 00:44:52,858
No, I, I don't care
if they print it.

908
00:44:52,991 --> 00:44:55,426
I should have done
Cortes and Montezuma.

909
00:44:55,560 --> 00:44:56,862
Cortes and Montezuma.

910
00:44:56,995 --> 00:45:00,065
I wanted Dustin Hoffman
and Warren Beatty.

911
00:45:00,198 --> 00:45:03,902
Hoffman as Cortes,
Beatty as Montezuma.

912
00:45:04,035 --> 00:45:05,904
An amazing story.

913
00:45:06,037 --> 00:45:10,541
Cortes: Arrogant, cruel,
chivalrous.

914
00:45:10,675 --> 00:45:15,380
Montezuma:
Painfully superstitious,
can't make a right move.

915
00:45:15,513 --> 00:45:18,016
It's a wonderful tale.

916
00:45:18,149 --> 00:45:19,851
I want to meet
Warren Beatty.

917
00:45:19,985 --> 00:45:21,719
You're too old
for Warren Beatty.

918
00:45:22,687 --> 00:45:24,422
I'm only 22.

919
00:45:24,555 --> 00:45:25,757
(PHONE RINGS)

920
00:45:25,891 --> 00:45:27,225
No, I got it.

921
00:45:27,893 --> 00:45:29,660
Hello?

922
00:45:29,795 --> 00:45:31,763
Yes, he is.
Just a minute, please.

923
00:45:31,897 --> 00:45:32,898
Harry?
Hmm.

924
00:45:33,031 --> 00:45:35,100
For you.
It's your son.

925
00:45:36,334 --> 00:45:37,568
My son?
Yeah.

926
00:45:44,242 --> 00:45:45,710
Gregory,
where the hell are you?

927
00:45:45,844 --> 00:45:47,245
GREGORY: (OVER PHONE)
I'm downstairs.

928
00:45:47,913 --> 00:45:48,947
Are you okay?

929
00:45:49,080 --> 00:45:50,115
I'm fine.

930
00:45:50,248 --> 00:45:51,282
You sure?

931
00:45:51,416 --> 00:45:52,818
I'm sure.
Can I come up?

932
00:45:52,951 --> 00:45:54,752
Okay, come right up.

933
00:45:57,555 --> 00:45:58,990
He flew in from L.A.

934
00:45:59,124 --> 00:46:00,558
He's okay?

935
00:46:00,691 --> 00:46:02,060
We'll soon find out.

936
00:46:02,193 --> 00:46:03,461
The drugs?

937
00:46:03,594 --> 00:46:06,097
He's clean.
He's A.A. for
a whole year now.

938
00:46:06,231 --> 00:46:08,633
Uh, maybe we can finish
this tomorrow, Mr. Stone.

939
00:46:08,766 --> 00:46:09,767
NANCY:
Oh, good idea.

940
00:46:09,901 --> 00:46:11,469
Oh, sure, uh,
come by for lunch.

941
00:46:11,602 --> 00:46:14,139
You're having lunch
with Ronnie Liebowitz
and Mike Krakower.

942
00:46:14,272 --> 00:46:15,273
Well, how about breakfast?

943
00:46:15,406 --> 00:46:16,908
Uh, fine. 9:00?

944
00:46:17,042 --> 00:46:18,243
No, make it 11:00.

945
00:46:18,376 --> 00:46:20,611
And nothing personal
about my son in your piece.

946
00:46:20,745 --> 00:46:21,679
(DOORBELL RINGS)

947
00:46:21,813 --> 00:46:23,114
Excuse me.

948
00:46:27,152 --> 00:46:28,486
You look older, Harry.

949
00:46:28,619 --> 00:46:30,088
But then again, so do I.

950
00:46:32,190 --> 00:46:33,158
(GRUNTS)

951
00:46:33,291 --> 00:46:35,927
Hi, Uncle Phil!
Long time no see.

952
00:46:36,061 --> 00:46:37,562
You look like
you got a toothache.

953
00:46:37,695 --> 00:46:38,997
Or, uh, or is that me?

954
00:46:41,900 --> 00:46:45,803
And this... This must be
Francoise. Hi, I'm Gregory,

955
00:46:45,937 --> 00:46:49,374
and I just flew in
on the transglobal
airlines' $99 special.

956
00:46:49,507 --> 00:46:52,043
No frills,
and also no engine.

957
00:46:52,177 --> 00:46:54,012
You must be the publicist.

958
00:46:54,145 --> 00:46:56,781
You look worried.
I assure you, I'm fine.

959
00:46:56,915 --> 00:46:58,616
Or is it The Pickle
you're worried about?

960
00:46:58,749 --> 00:46:59,985
(CHUCKLES)

961
00:47:00,118 --> 00:47:04,022
And you.
You're either
the Japanese exhibitor,

962
00:47:04,155 --> 00:47:05,924
or you're writing
my father's next film.

963
00:47:06,057 --> 00:47:07,758
I'm Yakimoto Yakimura.

964
00:47:07,893 --> 00:47:09,127
Of course.

965
00:47:09,260 --> 00:47:11,196
I loved your piece
on Sigourney Weaver
in The Times.

966
00:47:11,329 --> 00:47:14,165
And you did
something terrific
on Billy Wilder.

967
00:47:14,299 --> 00:47:15,867
And I do not use
that term loosely.

968
00:47:16,001 --> 00:47:17,002
Well, thank you.

969
00:47:17,135 --> 00:47:18,369
Uh, see you at 11:00, Harry?

970
00:47:18,503 --> 00:47:19,670
Yeah.

971
00:47:22,440 --> 00:47:24,075
What are you on, Gregory?

972
00:47:24,209 --> 00:47:27,845
You are absolutely gorgeous.

973
00:47:27,979 --> 00:47:29,347
Relax, Harry.
It's not a pass.

974
00:47:29,480 --> 00:47:31,316
You're on something
and I don't like it.

975
00:47:31,449 --> 00:47:33,618
Time to go.
See you tomorrow.

976
00:47:33,751 --> 00:47:36,554
Bye, Phil.
Good to see you.

977
00:47:36,687 --> 00:47:38,189
Oh, Francoise, bye-bye.
Bye.

978
00:47:38,323 --> 00:47:40,959
It was very nice to meet you.
Bye. Bye. Bye.

979
00:47:41,692 --> 00:47:42,727
I was right.

980
00:47:42,860 --> 00:47:44,996
That was the publicist,
wasn't it?

981
00:47:45,130 --> 00:47:46,297
Swear to me
you're clean.

982
00:47:46,431 --> 00:47:48,033
I swear to you, I'm clean.

983
00:47:48,166 --> 00:47:49,700
I'm clean a year
this Christmas, pop.

984
00:47:49,834 --> 00:47:52,103
I'm writing a movie
that's what I want
to talk to you about.

985
00:47:52,237 --> 00:47:54,072
And I wanna see The Pickle,
and mom,

986
00:47:54,205 --> 00:47:56,908
and Carrie,
Grandma Yetta, and the baby.

987
00:47:58,309 --> 00:47:59,744
The baby is beautiful.

988
00:48:00,545 --> 00:48:02,013
Adorable.

989
00:48:03,081 --> 00:48:05,383
Let's take a walk, pop.

990
00:48:05,516 --> 00:48:07,152
GREGORY:
It's a murder mystery.

991
00:48:07,285 --> 00:48:10,755
It all takes place
in Laurel Canyon.

992
00:48:10,888 --> 00:48:14,993
The detective
walks in a house,
picks up a cat.

993
00:48:15,126 --> 00:48:16,594
He says, "I wish
the hell you could talk."

994
00:48:16,727 --> 00:48:19,864
So the cat's the only
witness to the crime.

995
00:48:19,998 --> 00:48:21,967
The cat looks him
straight in the eye
and he says,

996
00:48:22,100 --> 00:48:24,102
"Look in the bathroom
under the sink."

997
00:48:24,235 --> 00:48:26,104
What do you mean,
"the cat says"?

998
00:48:26,237 --> 00:48:28,473
It's a talking cat.
It's funny.

999
00:48:30,741 --> 00:48:32,110
It's ridiculous.

1000
00:48:42,587 --> 00:48:45,123
Can I see
one of the new
blood pressure kits, please?

1001
00:48:45,256 --> 00:48:46,624
They just came in.

1002
00:48:46,757 --> 00:48:48,426
They are great.
Just a minute.

1003
00:48:48,559 --> 00:48:50,828
You just made a movie
about a flying pickle.

1004
00:48:50,962 --> 00:48:53,464
No one is gonna buy a script
about a talking cat.

1005
00:48:53,598 --> 00:48:54,966
Ronnie Liebowitz is.

1006
00:48:55,100 --> 00:48:56,767
Ronnie Liebowitz,
the head of the studio?

1007
00:48:56,901 --> 00:48:57,902
He loves it.

1008
00:48:58,036 --> 00:48:59,570
How did you meet him?

1009
00:48:59,704 --> 00:49:01,472
All you have to do...
I told him
I was your son.

1010
00:49:01,606 --> 00:49:03,508
Is insert your left
forefinger in the hole.

1011
